==English==

===Etymology===
''Paddle'' in the name refers to the riders arm action, the same as paddling a [[surfboard]], not to a separate physical [[paddle]] (no such paddle is used with this type of board).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[paddle]] [[board]]}}

# Large fat board used for [[surf life saving]].  Propelled by the rider using their arms, either lying face down or sitting up on their knees.  The board usually has straps positioned along the sides to hold onto.
#: 1997: ''you'd probably grab a paddle board and paddle out and grab them, instead of swimming out'' &mdash; Simone Cotter on ABC [[w:Radio National|Radio National]], ''Surf Lifesaving'', 17 October 1997 [http://www.ausport.gov.au/fulltext/1997/sportsf/sf971017.htm]